<doc id="1276820" wikidata="Q2890093" url="?curid=1276820" title="Battle of Seoul">
<text>The five battles of the Korean War fought in and around the city of Seoul are known as the Battle of Seoul:

*First Battle of Seoul – North Korean forces capture Seoul on June 28, 1950
*Second Battle of Seoul – United Nations forces capture Seoul from the North Koreans in September 1950, following the Battle of Inchon
*Third Battle of Seoul – The Chinese People&#x27;s Volunteer Army capture Seoul in January 1951
*Fourth Battle of Seoul – United Nations forces capture Seoul for the second time during Operation Ripper in March 1951.
*Fifth Battle of Seoul – The Chinese People&#x27;s Volunteer Army fail to recapture Seoul during the Chinese Spring Offensive in April 1951.</text><links>
