<doc id="1276962" wikidata="Q2112382" url="?curid=1276962" title="Eleonore Poelsleitner">
<text>Eleonore Polsleitner (born 2 October 1920) was a female guard at the Mauthausen concentration camp in Austria. Born in Unterach, Austria, Polsleitner became a female overseer at the Mauthausen-Gusen concentration camp on 1 November 1944. She trained under Jane Bernigau and has never been prosecuted for war crimes.

