<doc id="1276988" wikidata="Q179640" url="?curid=1276988" title="Catholic Private University Linz">
<text>The Catholic Private University Linz is one of four universities in Linz, the capital of Upper Austria, with approximately 500 students enrolled. Its roots go back to 1672 and it is a Papal faculty since 1978. It is an accredited private university but its tuition fees currently () match those of Austria&#x27;s public universities.

